cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.DS

The paper presents an approach to clustering using decision trees and instance-based learning, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The methodology is implemented in a system that uses logical decision tree representation (cs.CL) and is tested in both propositional and relational domains (cs.DB). The use of decision trees also suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
